(firstQuint)Rheumatoid Arthritis Response to Methotrexate.

 Rheumatoid arthritis patients with active disease who their rheumatologist prescribe methotrexate as a treatment will be included.

 Patients will participate in a prospective and observational study in which the response to methotrexate will be performed by ustrasound (US) of joints and tendons The main objective of the study is the change in B mode and Doppler mode US after 24 weeks of methotrexate treatment.

